properties.headline: Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued January 11 at 4:38PM CST until January 11 at 5:45PM CST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Tallahassee has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Western Jackson County in the Panhandle of Florida...
Northwestern Bay County in the Panhandle of Florida...
Southeastern Walton County in the Panhandle of Florida...
Central Holmes County in the Panhandle of Florida...
Washington County in the Panhandle of Florida...

* Until 545 PM CST.

* At 438 PM CST, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 9 miles southeast of Geneva to 19 miles south of
Santa Rosa Beach, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Panama City Beach, Vernon, Chipley, Graceville, Bonifay, Bradford,
Live Oak, Cottondale, Alford, Caryville, Wausau, Esto, Westville,
Ebro, Campbellton, Noma, Black, Whitehead Crossroads, Gulf Resort
Beach and West Panama City.
properties.instruction:
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CST for southeastern
Alabama...and the Panhandle of Florida.

Remain alert for a possible tornado! Tornadoes can develop quickly
from severe thunderstorms. If you spot a tornado go at once into the
basement or small central room in a sturdy structure.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.
